{
  "texts": [
    "Surprisingly, even small vertical adjustments can dramatically reduce the need for horizontal expansion, reducing the magnitude of rebalances and improving stability.",
    "E. ContributionsOur contributions are as follows: 1) Scaling Plane Model: A new two-dimensional abstraction for elastic database configurations.",
    "2) Analytical Performance Surfaces: Closed-form latency, throughput, cost, and coordination models.",
    "3) DiagonalScale Algorithm: A discrete optimization algorithm evaluating local neighborhoods in the H-V plane.",
    "4) Theory: Proof sketches of monotonic improvement, convergence to local optima, and stability guarantees."
  ]
}